{
  "stem": "18575.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 349.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a little boy, who spoke only German, who would join our classroom.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we used to make fun out of him because he couldn't-- you know, the sadistic kid stuff, they are-- because he couldn't speak Polish.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But he learned very fast.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That what I personally knew of Hitler.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Later, just-- just weeks before the war, we were kept [? tolding ?] the propaganda that, of course, that the war is imminent because the German Hitler demand that the corridor between East Prussia and German through Polish territory.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was almost an ultimatum.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The propaganda says that we have nothing to worry about because of the Germans, everything is a ersatz, which ersatz means in German, it's artificial, synthetic, so to say.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Ersatz means synthetic, artificial-- that the tanks are paper tigers that we can defend.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I believed it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was a patriot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I believed that-- that we can hold them back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I know of-- there were articles in Polish newspapers, anti-Nazi articles, anti-Germans.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the government confiscated papers not trying-- because they must have been protests from Germany-- confiscated the papers just before the war.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I recall there was a poem, that is a great poem, in one of the papers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I still recall that poem, [NON-ENGLISH], which, if you allow me, just I'll give you a short thing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The poem was called 'Dreams.' And it says, people have varied dreams, and it's a fantastic thing to dream.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "While sometimes it's happy, sometimes sad, and sometimes a very bitter, very bad.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he says, I saw it-- a world-- I dream of a world who believed in sin and broke-- abolished the-- the law and beauty.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And those that have shown the greatest horror were called the lords of the world.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
